An NGO, Teen Ambassadors Foundation (TAF), has organised a medical outreach for residents of Luvu Madaki community in Karu Local Government Area of Nasarawa State. The medical intervention included screening and treatment for malaria, typhoid, ulcer, urinary tract infections, hypertension, diabetes, skin diseases, hepatitis B and C, as well as pelvic inflammatory diseases. ‘FCT school feeding will be sustained despite rising cost of foodstuff’ Foundation donates foodstuff, pays school fees for orphans Doctors, nurses, laboratory scientists and pharmacists were on the ground to offer services free of charge to adults and children.